    "description": {
      "value": "<h2></b>Description</b></h2></p><p>These ceramic statuettes are molded in the likenesses of armored soldiers, horses, or dogs, and are considered symbols of good fortune in battle. Once per day, the possessor of a terra-cotta talisman can reroll a single attack roll as an immediate action, with a +1 luck bonus on the reroll, and keep the most favorable result. A terra-cotta talisman also contains the vestige of a spirit of an ancient warrior or warbeast that can be called upon once per day as a standard action to manifest itself as a spiritual force. The powers of the talismans are as follows:  • Terra-Cotta Horse: phantom steed  • Terra-Cotta Hound: mage's faithful hound  • Terra-Cotta Warrior: spiritual ally<br><p><b>Base Item:</b> </p><h3><b>Requirements</b></h3><p>Craft Wondrous Item, borrow fortune (see page 206 of the Pathfinder RPG Advanced Player's Guide),  mage's faithful hand</p><h3><b>Source: </b></h3>AP 51",
